# lang

TypeScript (Node.js v20+ / ESM). All exports are pure ESM ‚Äî no CommonJS.

# deps

- `eslint` + `@eslint/js` ‚Äî core linting engine and JS recommended rules
- `typescript-eslint` + `@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin` + `@typescript-eslint/parser` ‚Äî TypeScript-aware linting and type-checked rules
- `eslint-plugin-import-x` + `eslint-import-resolver-typescript` ‚Äî import order enforcement with TypeScript path resolution
- `eslint-plugin-prettier` + `eslint-config-prettier` + `prettier` ‚Äî Prettier formatting enforced as an ESLint rule, conflicts disabled
- `prettier-eslint` ‚Äî runs Prettier then ESLint for formatting pipelines
- `prettier-plugin-astro` ‚Äî Prettier support for `.astro` files
- `prettier-plugin-multiline-arrays` ‚Äî formats long arrays across multiple lines
- `prettier-plugin-packagejson` ‚Äî sorts and formats `package.json` fields
- `@ianvs/prettier-plugin-sort-imports` ‚Äî deterministic import ordering via Prettier
- `globals` ‚Äî environment global variable sets (node, browser, etc.)
- `jiti` ‚Äî runtime TypeScript import support for config files
- `@openhint/preset-typescript` ‚Äî workspace TypeScript preset; `tsconfig.json` extends its `node.json`

# build

- Consumed directly as TypeScript source ‚Äî no separate compile step for the preset itself
- Downstream packages import specific config variants: `import config from '@openhint/preset-eslint/node'`
- Each package's `eslint.config.ts` spreads the imported config array and adds project-specific overrides

# lib @openhint/preset-eslint

Exports three composable ESLint flat config arrays ‚Äî `base`, `node`, and `isomorphic` ‚Äî each targeting a different runtime environment. All three build on a shared base that wires up TypeScript-ESLint, import ordering, and Prettier as a linter rule.

# good

- Always spread the preset config inside `defineConfig` and layer overrides on top ‚Äî never replace the base outright.
- The `import-x` resolver must always point to the consuming package's `tsconfig.json` to resolve path aliases correctly.
- Prettier must remain the canonical formatter; ESLint formatting rules are intentionally disabled via `eslint-config-prettier` to avoid conflicts.

# bad

- Do not enable `@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any` ‚Äî it is explicitly turned off to allow gradual typing in utility and config code.
- Do not re-enable `@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars` ‚Äî it produces false positives on type-only declarations; TypeScript's own checks are sufficient.
- Do not add environment globals directly to the base config ‚Äî use the `node` or `isomorphic` variants which scope globals to their runtime.
